37 SECTION 6. ORS 456.559 is amended to read:
38 456.559. (1) The Housing and Community Services Department shall:
39 (a) Maintain current housing data and information concerning available programs, status of
40 funding, programs planned or undertaken which might conflict with, overlap, duplicate or supersede
41 other planned or existing programs and call these to the attention of appropriate state agencies,
42 governmental bodies and public or private housing sponsors.
43 (b) Maintain current data on publicly supported housing as provided under ORS 456.824.
44 (c) Provide to appropriate state agencies, governmental bodies and public or private housing
45 sponsors such advisory and educational services as will assist them in the development of housing
[7]

A-Eng. HB 4036
1 plans and projects.
2 (d) Subject to the approval of the Oregon Housing Stability Council, make noninterest bearing
3 advances, in accordance with ORS 456.710 and the policies of the department, to qualified nonprofit
4 sponsors for development costs of housing projects until mortgage funds are released to repay the
5 advances as provided in ORS 456.710.
6 (e) Advise and assist appropriate state agencies, governmental bodies and public or private
7 housing sponsors, cities and counties, in all programs and activities which are designed or might
8 tend to fulfill the purposes of ORS 456.548 to 456.828 and ORS chapter 458.
9 (f) Encourage and assist in the planning, development, construction, rehabilitation and conser-
10 vation of dwelling units for persons and families of lower income.
11 (g) Be the central state department to apply for, receive and distribute, on behalf of appropriate
12 state agencies, governmental bodies and public or private housing sponsors in the state, grants, gifts,
13 contributions, loans, credits or assistance from the federal government or any other source for
14 housing programs except when the donor, grantor, or lender of such funds specifically directs some
15 other agency to administer them. Moneys received under this section shall be deposited with the
16 State Treasurer in an account separate and distinct from the General Fund. Interest earned by the
17 account shall be credited to the account.
18 (h) For the purposes of acquiring moneys, credits or other assistance from any agency or
19 instrumentality of the United States or from any public corporation chartered by the United States,
20 comply with any applicable agreements or restrictions for the receipt of such assistance and become
21 a member of any such association or public corporation chartered by the United States.
22 (i) Assist individuals, appropriate state agencies, governmental bodies and public or private
23 housing sponsors through a program which provides housing information, planning, educational
24 services and technical assistance.
25 (j) Comply with the requirements of ORS 443.225 in assisting in the development of any housing
26 for residential care, training or treatment for persons with intellectual or developmental disabilities
27 or mental or emotional disturbances.
28 (2) Except as otherwise provided in ORS 456.625 (7), 456.766 to 456.828, 458.315 (3) and 458.480
29 to 458.490 and section 2 of this 2026 Act, the department may not itself develop, construct, reha-
30 bilitate or conserve housing units; and neither the department nor any housing sponsor, including
31 but not limited to any association, corporation, cooperative housing authority or urban renewal
32 agency organized to provide housing and other facilities under ORS 456.548 to 456.828, may own,
33 acquire, construct, purchase, lease, operate or maintain utility facilities, including facilities for the
34 generation of electricity, for the distribution of gas and electricity, and for the conveyance of tele-
35 phone and telegraph messages.
36 (3) In accordance with the provisions of this section and with the advice of the council, the
37 department shall establish statewide priorities for housing programs. State agencies shall coordinate
38 their housing programs with the department. All state agencies intending to apply for federal funds
39 for use in planning, developing or managing housing, or rendering assistance to governmental bodies
40 or sponsors or individuals involved therein shall submit a description of the proposed activity to the
41 department for review not less than 30 days prior to the intended date of submission of the appli-
42 cation to the federal agency. The department shall determine whether the proposal would result in
43 a program that would overlap, duplicate or conflict with any other housing program in the state. If
44 the department finds overlapping or duplication or conflict, it shall recommend modifications in the
45 application. The Oregon Department of Administrative Services shall consider these recommen-
[8]

A-Eng. HB 4036
1 dations in making its decision to approve or disapprove the application. The department shall com-
2 plete its review and forward its recommendations within 15 working days after receipt of the
3 notification. Failure of the department to complete the review within that time shall constitute ap-
4 proval of the application by the department.
5 (4) The Director of the Housing and Community Services Department may participate in dis-
6 cussions and deliberations of the council. The director may suggest policies to the council, including
7 those necessary to stimulate and increase the supply of housing for persons and families of lower
8 income.
9 SECTION 7. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public
10 peace, health and safety, an emergency is declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect
11 on its passage.
